==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nestling
<hw>Nes"tling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A young
bird which has not abandoned the nest.</def> <rj><au>Piers
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A nest; a receptacle.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nestling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nestling
<hw>Nes"tling</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Newly hatched; being yet in the
nest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nestor</ent>⟦br⟧
